ENTRY            A1511   20260318   20260508   20260508       A133
SUBENT        A1511001   20260318   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                 10         23
TITLE      The 7Li(alpha,n)10B0 differential cross section for
           alpha-energies of up to 8 MeV
AUTHOR     (L.Van Der Zwan,K.W.Geiger)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,180,615,1972)
INSTITUTE  (1CANOTC)
FACILITY   (VDG,1CANOTC) 4 MV Van de Graaff accelerator
MONITOR    (3-LI-7(A,N)5-B-10,,SIG)
           At energies below E = 5.51 MeV (threshold for n1
           neutrons) the measurements were normalized to the
           neutron production cross section of Gibbons et al.
           later revised downwards by the same authors
            (R.L.Macklin et al.).
MONIT-REF  (T0010002,J.H.Gibbons+,J,PR,114,571,1959)
           (P0117012,R.L.Macklin+,J,PR,165,1147,1968)
SAMPLE     7Li metal (0.007% 6Li) onto a tantalum backing. The
           target thickness was between 50 and 150 ug/cm2
           and selected such that for a particular run the maximum
           alpha-energy beam spread did not exceed 100 keV. The
           thickness was determined to within 10%
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Uncertainty in target thickness
HISTORY    (19800814C) Compilation produced by RFNC-VNIIEF Sarov
           (19990323U)CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year and lower cases.
           (20260318A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              23
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
     10.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           30
SUBENT        A1511002   20260318   20260508   20260508       A133
BIB                  8         18
REACTION   (3-LI-7(A,N)5-B-10,PAR,DA)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) Proton recoil detector consisted either of a
           stilbene crystal of 0.5 cm length and 2.5 cm diam., or
           a NE 213 liquid scintillator with the following inside
           dim.: length 0.63 cm, diam. 1.26 cm. The scintillators
           were coupled to an RCA 8575 photomultiplier.
           Crystal of 0.5 cm length and 2.5 cm diameter.
           (LONGC) A precision long counter (see REL-REF).
REL-REF    (I,,J.DePangher+,R,BNWL-260,1966) - Detect. descript.
METHOD     (PSD)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-SYS) Systematic errors
           (ERR-S) Statistical errors
FLAG       (1.) Tabulated values from the text
STATUS     (CURVE,,L.Van Der Zwan+,J,NP/A,180,615,1972) Fig 3
           (TABLE,,L.Van Der Zwan+,J,NP/A,180,615,1972) Text
           on p.618 (see FLAG)
HISTORY    (20260318A) SD: EN-ERR->EN-ERR-DIG; DATA-ERR->ERR-DIG;
           ERR-1 -> ERR-SYS. BIB updated.
ENDBIB              18
